  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nWhen starting a new project, not touching the config, and running `truffle test`; I would expect Truffle to spin up a `truffle develop` instance without any networks supplied. Instead, it throws.\r\n\r\nWe could improve new developer DX by adding this functionality.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. `truffle init <any_name>`\r\n2. Add a smart contract and corresponding test\r\n3. `truffle test` throws, noting the contract hasn't been deployed to the given network\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nTruffle will automatically use a `truffle develop` instance to run the tests.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n`truffle test` throws, noting the contract hasn't been deployed to the given network\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: macOS Ventura 13.1\r\n* Ethereum client: N/A\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.7.5\r\n* node version (`node --version`): 18.12.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 9.1.1\r\n",
